Excellente prof! Ses cours sont très chargés et elle passe au travers de la matière assez rapidement. Cependant elle est disponible en dehors des heures de classes et prend la peine de bien répondre à tous les questions lorsqu'il y en a.

Eva is an AMAZING prof - I don't understand her poor ratings. She's super patient with questions, replies really fast to her emails (her answers to your questions are very detailed and clear). Also grades the tests really fast. No surprises on midterms/exams if you do all the practice questions. I highly recommend her!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Dr. Hemmer is one of the best chemistry teacher I've had; I truly don't get her poor rating. It's true that this course is a lot of work and that there are a lot of slides (850+) to review for the final. However, she will always answer your questions inside and outside of class and if you do the homework every week, you will get a good mark.

You get an additional 5% on your final mark if you participate in class. Class avg. so low that our final mark is boosted by 10% if we submitted homeworks in a timely matter. The class in general is very content heavy (mix of gen chem, orgo, inorgo, phys chem) and each midterm was about 500 -700 slides to study.  the final was only tricks,have fun!

Good prof, a new professor but she's doing a really good job already. Class average is 80% and she gave bonus marks. Would recommend she really cares about her students, the class is easy and an easy A if you do the work.
So much material, she's making me cry really. Worst class I've ever took
Good prof! She rocks take her!

Please AVOID this professor. In my whole bachelor degree, I've never had to deal with that kind of professor. We have over 1000 slides for the final exam and it's cumulative. She sprint through her 80 slides per class and barely answer questions. Most stressful class in 4 years.

I was really excited tontakenthis class at the beginning of the year. As a straight A student, I find this class to be an overall waste of time. She is a new professor, but she's one of the worst prof I've ever had, she doesn't care a second about our small group. Midterm average was a D, and she makes me hate chemistry, course could be much funner

She is rude and Condescending, She will berates students in front of the whole class and laughs when students ask questions.  She does not explain the material thoroughly and says we should "just look it up"  because she's not here to answer questions all day.  Overall the Worst professor I've had so far

There's nothing nice to say about this prof.  Her powerpoints are over 100 slides each and she powers through them in class to finish them within 80 minutes.  Fill in the blanks and no full powerpoints.  Very rude.  She will tell you you're not independent if you ask questions.  Midterm very long.  She will not give you any hints on what to study.

This professor is AWFUL. She doesn't answer any questions that you ask (she says that "you need to be more independent, this isn't high school anymore"), although it's her job to help. Read the slides word for word and skims over it way too quickly. Lectures notes are fill-in-the-blanks but she doesn't post the complete version. AVOID AT ALL  COST!

Difficult to understand her expectations of students. Unfriendly when asking questions, especially during class. Fill in the blanks on lecture slides. Does not post full lectures afterwards. Reads slides without providing background explanations. Always seems pressed for time during lectures which causes her to lecture very quickly.

This class material is not particularly difficult. I absolutely despise this class due to the fact that Dr. Hemmer told us we would be unable to get a degree by asking her questions.
